                        <summary/>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                            <locus from="7v" to="242v"/>
                            <title>Pentaglot Glossary: Gǝʿǝz — Amharic — Tigrinya — Tigre — Swedish</title>
                            <note>According to <bibl><ptr target="bm:Strelcyn1976Catalogue"/><citedRange unit="page">50</citedRange>
                                <citedRange unit="page">147</citedRange></bibl>, the Amharic column and the introduction are identical to
                                <bibl><ptr target="bm:Tayya1889Sawasew"/><citedRange unit="chapter">3</citedRange></bibl> and do contain 
                                also cross-refernences. Therefore the text probably represents the original version of the printed edition. Both the Amharic
                                and the Gǝʿǝz as well as possibly the Tigrinya columns can therefore be assumed to come from the hand of
                                <persName ref="PRS9347TayyaGa"><roleName type="title">ʾAlaqa</roleName> Tāyya</persName>.</note>
                            <textLang mainLang="am" otherLangs="gez ti sv tig"/>
                            <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.1">
                                <locus from="7v"/>
                                <title>Amharic introduction</title>
                                <textLang mainLang="am"/>
                                <incipit xml:lang="am">ሶስተኛ፡ ታላቅ፡ ክፍል፡ ነጠላ፡ ግሥና፡ ዘርና፡ ነባር። ነጠላ፡ ግሥ፡ ዘርና፡ ነባር፡ ምን፡ እንደሆኑ፡ በመቅድሙ፡ በገጽ፡ ፬ ሶስተኛውን፡
                                    ክፍል፡ እይ። ሞክሽ፡ ያላቸው፡ ግሦች፡ ባራት፡ ክፍል፡ ይከፈላሉ።</incipit> 
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.2">
                                <locus from="8v" to="242v"/>
                                <title>Pentaglot Glossary</title>
                                <note>Gǝʿǝz and Amharic are written in the same hand and with the same pen, possibly that of 
                                    <persName ref="PRS9347TayyaGa"><roleName type="title">ʾAlaqa</roleName> Tāyya</persName>.
                                    The Gǝʿǝz and Amharic verbs are placed in the left and middle columns of the 
                                    verso pages, while the Tigrinya verbs were added in the right column, probably by Tāyya but with another pen. 
                                    The Tigre and Swedish equivalents, however, are written by another, European hand in the left and right columns of 
                                    the recto pages vis-à-vis the Gǝʿǝz — Amharic — Tigrinya polyglot glossary. Interlinear corrections on the Amharic 
                                    part may have been added by the author after the experience of printing the first and second chapters of the Sawāsǝw
                                    were printed. The last eleven lemmata from 
                                    <bibl><ptr target="bm:Tayya1889Sawasew"/><citedRange unit="page">189</citedRange></bibl>
                                    are missing because the last folium is lost. The Tigre vocabulary was apparently not used in 
                                    <bibl><ptr target="bm:LittmannHofner1962Tigre"/></bibl>.</note>
                                <textLang mainLang="am" otherLangs="gez ti sv tig"/>
                                <explicit xml:lang="tig"><supplied resp="PRS8999Strelcyn" reason="lost">ኩፕ፡ አ</supplied>ፍንጫ።
                                    <gap reason="lost"/></explicit> <!-- Which languages are these words? -->  
                            </msItem>
                        </msItem>
